-- China Punishes Officials for Corruption in Construction: Xinhua
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2011-12-21T13:44:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/china-punishes-officials-for-corruption-in-construction-xinhua.html
A total of 15,109 Chinese officials
were punished in the past two years for construction-related
corruption or dereliction of duty, Xinhua News Agency said
today, citing a central government agency it didnâ€™t identify.  The officials received disciplinary or administrative
penalties between July 2009 and November 2011, and 7,891 cases
were transferred to judicial organs for handling, the official
news service reported.  China  has checked all government-funded
building projects initiated and conducted since 2008, it said.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
